reviews.review_text: By the way ... The Sugaree is friggin' EPIC!!!!!!!

Healy AUD At The Board ??? I received this copy from bt.etree.com a few years ago and was very impressed with it's dynamics.  If I recall, I think one of the comments from the peanut gallery was that this was an audience recording from Dan Healy at the board.  Whether that's true or not is anybody's guess, since this upload is also unattributed.  Personally, I didn't even know he made AUDs.  But if it's true, it shows in being a wonderfully dynamic recording.  The other AUD ((FOB, unknown mics)> MC> DAT> CDR> EAC> SHN; like a reseed of SHN ID 4954) is as equal good as this one.  

Since Richie Stankiewicz has lost his first set tape, his 2nd Set equals this recording with its dynamics.  But It seems that Rich was just in front of the board since there seems to be a touch more distance with this recording. Ten rows at the most.   Both are excellent recordings.  The only down side for this one is that Iko through Alabama are missing, being replaced by the board, which is very unfortunate.

The Friend AUD recording has better ambiance since he lets his tape run almost uninterrupted through the entire show.  I have kept all four audience recordings since they all deserve collecting.

This is one of the best shows the band ever did.  Yeah 
 MVotter, the Sugaree is an incredible #2 right behind the best ever done on 5/22/77.
